The paper discusses expert finding in academic digital libraries, which involves information retrieval techniques and analysis of citation patterns. Therefore, cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.DL (Digital Libraries), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) are likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of profile information about experts, which could fall under cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) or cs.DB (Databases).
